processing and human understanding. \n\nPhilosophically, the debate hinges on whether functional equivalence (AI's behavior) suffices for mental equivalence (human-like cognition). While some (e.g., functionalists) argue it does, others (e.g., biological naturalists) contend that only systems with the right biological substrate (e.g., brains) can have genuine mental states. The statement implicitly adopts the functionalist view without acknowledging the contestation."
}

